      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/6a8cbe/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2022-12-07T02:43:57.538Z",
      "cooked": "<p>AGree w/ Alex, your best bet is to slowly increase the duration up to the expected time (or say 80% of the duration you expect to finish your event) . since you have long distance running experience, the training stress / style would be approximately the same.</p>\n<p>You can also choose to train based on the expected TSS(or Load) you will experience on the event. Then build up to it.</p>\n<p>YOu can use intervals.icu to plan your training and use the the FITNESS chart to monitor / plan your progress.</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/2a84e9060182ce69f89ced1558091e00563a5741.png\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\">\n      <a href=\"https://forum.intervals.icu/t/planning-a-plan-around-fitness-charts/1757/9\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"12:23PM - 09 December 2020\">Intervals.icu Forum \u2013 9 Dec 20</a>\n  </header>\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/416;\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/f/f2da3c45d1f39a89e8be5342ce6184a901e48b01_2_690x416.png\" class=\"thumbnail\" width=\"690\" height=\"416\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/f/f2da3c45d1f39a89e8be5342ce6184a901e48b01_2_690x416.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/f/f2da3c45d1f39a89e8be5342ce6184a901e48b01_2_1035x624.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/f/f2da3c45d1f39a89e8be5342ce6184a901e48b01_2_1380x832.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/f/f2da3c45d1f39a89e8be5342ce6184a901e48b01_2_10x10.png\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://forum.intervals.icu/t/planning-a-plan-around-fitness-charts/1757/9\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Planning a plan around Fitness Charts</a></h3>\n\n<p>Hello,  I have also been working on this topic for some time. When training outside, the training control via CTL works very well and gives me a good feedback of my load and recovery.  When training indoors in winter on the smarttrainer, it looks...</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/2a84e9060182ce69f89ced1558091e00563a5741.png\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\">\n      <a href=\"https://forum.intervals.icu/t/future-fitness-changes/1465/23?u=app4g\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"10:59AM - 20 February 2022\">Intervals.icu Forum \u2013 20 Feb 22</a>\n  </header>\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/259;\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/7/711573c31aaf66974df96f4360dfa74064a1eb29_2_690x259.jpeg\" class=\"thumbnail\" width=\"690\" height=\"259\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/7/711573c31aaf66974df96f4360dfa74064a1eb29_2_690x259.jpeg, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/7/711573c31aaf66974df96f4360dfa74064a1eb29_2_1035x388.jpeg 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/7/711573c31aaf66974df96f4360dfa74064a1eb29_2_1380x518.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/7/711573c31aaf66974df96f4360dfa74064a1eb29_2_10x10.png\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://forum.intervals.icu/t/future-fitness-changes/1465/23?u=app4g\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Future fitness changes</a></h3>\n\n<p>I\u2019ll second the suggestion to do the low volume plan, and add a long Z2+3 ride of your choice (when and duration). Doesn\u2019t have to be one only, but at least all should be LIT.  Your CTL has plateaued, so there isn\u2019t much stimulus to achieve super...</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
